parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion-Induced Failure of Front and Rear Cross Members and Control Arms
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion-induced failure of the front and rear cross members and control arms can cause loss of steering control, wheel detachment, and accidents, leading to potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Abnormal loud clunking or grinding sounds
loud noise from the front or rear of the vehicle
tires rubbing against the fender or body
and sudden failure of the suspension system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Acceleration Failure due to Faulty Accelerator Pedal Position Sensor
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the accelerator pedal position sensor can cause the vehicle to hesitate or fail to accelerate, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: the vehicle fails to respond to acceleration attempts
the vehicle will not accelerate above a certain speed (e.g.
the check engine warning light remains illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Leaks into the Front Driver Side Floorboard
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaks into the front driver side floorboard can cause damage to electrical components, carpets, and upholstery, and may lead to mold and mildew growth, creating an unhealthy environment for occupants.
symptoms: Water accumulation in the front driver side floorboard
with no apparent opening of doors or windows.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Body Weld Failure in the Driver-Side Pillar
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of body welds in the driver-side pillar can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, potentially affecting its crash-worthiness, especially in the event of a side impact.
symptoms: Rubbing of body panels producing a high-pitched metallic sound
indicating a lack of or failed welds in the driver-side pillar.
